						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up near Kalamēs11vara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Rāmachandra—A.D. 1285.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">16th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandrarāya Svabhānu, Māgha śu. 1, Monday.</hi> In <hi rend="italic">Subhānu</hi> = A.D. 1284 <hi rend="italic">Māgha śu.</hi> 1 fell on Thursday, January 20. In the next year <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Tāraṇa, the details regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1285, January 8, Monday.</hi> The latter probably is the intended date.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of a hero (name lost) and seems to register a grant of land made in his memory.</p>						

						</summary>
